* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ˌstɛ.ɡʌnˈɔ.ɡɹʌ.fi/|lang=en}}
* {{audio|en-us-steganography.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun|-}}

# The practice of [[hiding]] [[message]]s, so that the presence of the message itself is hidden, often by writing them in places where they may not be found until someone finds the secret message in whatever is being used to hide it.
# Specifically: the use of small [[file]]s in [[computer]]s to communicate [[secret]] information. Compare [[cryptography]] for a more general idea.

====Usage notes====
Steganography differs from [[cryptography]] in that cryptography conceals only the content of the message through [[encryption]]. Steganography conceals the presence of the message itself.

